# textdomain: mcl_observers
Observer=Detektor
Emits redstone pulse when block in front changes=Vyzařuje redstone signál ve chvíli, kdy se blok prřd ním změní
An observer is a redstone component which observes the block in front of it and sends a very short redstone pulse whenever this block changes.=Pozorovatel je redstone komponenta, která pozoruje blok před sebou a vysílá velmi krátký redstonový impuls, kdykoli se tento blok změní.
Place the observer directly in front of the block you want to observe with the “face” looking at the block. The arrow points to the side of the output, which is at the opposite side of the “face”. You can place your redstone dust or any other component here.=
